Now I understand the issue. The `emails` variable on line 43-47 is computed as:

```ts
const emails = Array.from(new Set(players.flatMap((player) => {
    const verifiedExtraEmails = player.extraEmails.filter((playerEmail) => playerEmail.verified);
    const preferredExtraEmails = verifiedExtraEmails.length > 0 ? verifiedExtraEmails : player.extraEmails;
    return [player.accountEmail, ...preferredExtraEmails.map((playerEmail) => playerEmail.email)];
```

Normalizing and filtering each email, then joining them together. If all emails normalize to empty strings, the result is just an empty string, which means the form can still be submitted with `to: ''`. I need to disable the submit button when there are no valid emails and add a message explaining why.

Let me check the existing tests to see what needs updating.
