543	     * non-null team) are included. Players who have never played are skipped,
544	     * but their place in the introducer chain is preserved: each played
545	     * player's effective parent is the nearest ancestor in the `introducedBy`
546	     * chain who has also played.
547	     *
548	     * After computing effective parents, the tree is further pruned to players
549	     * who either have an effective parent or are themselves the effective
550	     * introducer of at least one other played player. Played players with no
551	     * connection to anyone else are excluded.
552	     *
553	     * A single founder is identified as the first played player with no
554	     * effective parent who is also an effective introducer. Any remaining
555	     * parentless players (orphans) are attached as children of the founder.
556	     *
557	     * If no founder can be identified (e.g. the data contains only circular
558	     * references or no connections at all), an empty virtual root node named
559	     * "Toastboy FC" is returned with no children.
560	     *
561	     * @returns A promise resolving to a single {@link FamilyTreeNodeType} root
562	     * node whose children form the complete introduction tree.
563	     */
